Hmm - my memory is hazy, but isn't there an SMTP response which says
&lt;foo&gt; isn't here, hes at &lt;bar&gt; and I ain't gonna forward it?

I wonder if any hosts can automatically parse the smtp response and
automatically redirect the message.

The thing we could do that doesn't require ANY hacks to the system
(except the naming) is use an address form like
&lt;list-name&gt;@&lt;list-name&gt;.maillist.  I'm not saying I like having to
double the name, but at least it would work.

Mike

